Movements, Home range and Social organization.
The Argentine
Serotine is usually found in colonies of 10-20 individuals, but colonies of 100 and even 100,000 individuals (
Mexico
) have been reported. It will share roosts with Jamaican Fruit-eating Bats (Artibeusjamaicensis), Great Fruit-eating Bats (A. lituratus), Toltec Fruit-eating Bats (A. toltecus), Little Yellow-shouldered Bats (Sturnira lilium), Common Vampire Bats (Desmodus rotundus), Black-winged Little Yellow Bats (
Rhogeessa tumida
), and Mexican Dog-faced Bats (Cynomops 
mexicanus
).
